==English==

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌk|-ʌk]]

===Noun===
'''shuck'''  (''plural:'' '''[[shucks]]''')
# The shell section, especially in relation to [[grain]]s such as [[corn]].

See also [[husk]].

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|shuck||}}
# To remove from a shell, especially in relation to [[grain]]s such as [[corn]].
# To split open a shell (with a knife), especially [[mollusc]]s such as [[oyster]]s.
# To remove an outer covering.
#*He '''shucked''' his clothes and dived naked into the pool.